# Shared-By-Default Architecture

Every new game mechanic, rule, or feature must work across **all modes** (offline/AI, tournament, bust, online) unless explicitly told otherwise.

## Where New Code Goes

| What | Where |
|---|---|
| New card rule / game mechanic | `lib/shared/engine/game_engine.dart` — `_applySpecialEffect`, `validatePlay`, or a new shared function |
| New win/loss condition | `lib/shared/rules/win_condition_rules.dart` |
| New penalty/chain rule | `lib/shared/rules/pickup_chain_rules.dart` |
| Mode-specific setup (deck, hand size, round config) | A config object passed as a parameter to `TableScreen`, NOT a new parallel screen |
| Bust-specific meta-game (rounds, elimination) | `lib/features/bust/` — orchestrates `TableScreen`, does not reimplement it |
| New UI screen | Only justified if the UI is genuinely different (e.g. `BustEliminationScreen`), never for different game logic |

## Mandatory Server Sync

Whenever `lib/shared/engine/game_engine.dart` changes, **also update** `server/lib/game_session.dart` to call the new/changed function. The server is the authoritative online engine — it must stay in sync.

## Anti-Patterns to Reject

```dart
// ❌ BAD — parallel screen that reimplements game loop
class NewModeGameScreen extends StatefulWidget {
  // 1000+ lines duplicating validatePlay, applyPlay, AI scheduling...
}

// ✅ GOOD — thin coordinator that configures TableScreen
class NewModeCoordinator extends StatelessWidget {
  Widget build(BuildContext context) => TableScreen(
    newModeConfig: NewModeConfig(...),
    onRoundComplete: _handleRoundComplete,
  );
}
```

```dart
// ❌ BAD — rule only in offline engine
void _applySpecialEffect(...) {
  // new card effect only here
}

// ✅ GOOD — rule in shared engine, consumed by all modes
// lib/shared/engine/game_engine.dart
GameState _applySpecialEffect(GameState gs, CardModel card, ...) {
  case Rank.newCard:
    return gs.copyWith(newEffect: ...);
}
// server/lib/game_session.dart already calls applyPlay() → picks it up automatically
```

## Checklist for Any New Feature

- [ ] Game logic added to `lib/shared/engine/game_engine.dart` (not a feature folder)
- [ ] `server/lib/game_session.dart` updated if engine API changed
- [ ] `test/engine_test.dart` has tests covering the new logic
- [ ] No new parallel game screen created (use `TableScreen` with a config param)
- [ ] `docs/rules-by-mode.md` updated if the rule affects gameplay
